 left his maternal justiucts un\n\u201cgUo prospedul- or' oty Avgd AL\nPROSPERITY DAY RE\nSTORES THE IDLE MEN\nSt. Louis, June I\u2014Thousands of\nmen thrown out by employment dur.\ning the business and financial depres\nsion are back in their old places to\nday, as the result of a concerted plan\nof all the manufacturing and commer\ncial concerns in the city to make this\n\u2018\u2018employment day\u2019\u2019. The project\nhas ite origin with the National\nProsperity assocation, \u2018the \u2018\u2018let us\nalone\u2019\u2019 body, and has been goeneral.\nly taken up by the business interests\nof the city.\nAmong the big concerns which\ncelebrated \u2018\u2018prosperity day\u2019' were\nthe Ferguson-McKinney Dry Goods\ncompany, which put back 1,000 em\nployes temporarily dropped from the\npay rolls during the financial depres\nsion and the Ely and Walker Dry\nGoods company, wheh today started\novery machine in its factories and\ngave employment to 2,000 men and\nwomen,\nMany other concerns employed\namaller numbers of workmen and the\nmovement hns been taken up by the\nraflroads aud other corporations.\nThere is a feeling of confidence that\n\u2018\u2018employment day'\u2019' marks the full\nreturn of prosperity to St. Louis, and\nit is likely that the plan followed\nhere will be taken up in many other\noities throughout the ocountry.\nFEMININE DEMONSTRATION\nLondon, June I\u2014What will prob\nably be the greatest demonstration\nfor the emancipation of womwen {n\nthe history of the world will be held\nfu Hyde Park on June 21, when it {s\nexpected that no less than 200,000\nsuffragottes will march through the\nstreots and liold public meetings in\nthe park, J\nANNAPOLIS GRADUATES\nLARGEST CLASS EVER\nAnnapolis, Md,, June I\u2014[lo lar.\ngest olass that over loft.the Anuapo.\nlis Naval acadomy at one time will\nbe graduamted this week, the com\nmencement week oxercises for the 200\nmidshipmen begiuning today with\nhe official reception to the board of\nCOMFORTING WORDS.\ninnny a Florence Household Will\nFind Them So.\nTo have the pains and aches of a\nbad back removed; to be entirely\nfree from avnoying, dangerous uri\nuary disorders is enough to make any\nkidney sufferer grateful. To tell\nhow this great change cau be brought\nabout will prove comforting words\nto hundreds of Floreuce readers.\nMrs. J. R. Wood, of 728 W. First\nBt., Florence, 0010, says: \u2018\u2018l have\nused Doan\u2019s Kidney Pills and am\nfirmly convinoed of their great value.\nPain 1n my left side annoyed me con\nsiderably, especially when I walked\nstooped or lited. Knowing that this\nwas caused by disordered kidneys I\nwas led to try Doan's Kidney Pills,\nas I had seen them highly recom\nmended for such troubles. My son\nprocured box for me at Daniels\u2019\ndrug store, and a marked improve\nment was the result of a short use of\nthem. Doan\u2019s Kidney pills are won\nderfully effective and I heartily rec\nommend them,\nFor sale by all dealers. Price 50\ncents. Foster-Milburn Co., Buffalo,\nNew York, sole agents for the United\nStates. Remember the name\u2014Doans\n\u2014and take no other. mwf\n\u2018vlsltors. During the next four days\n\u2018there will be the usual round of drills\nand practical exercises, Friday will\nbe commencement day, and it is ex\npected that Secretary Metcalf will\ndeliver an address and present the\ndiplomas to the graduates. On Sat\nurday the first, second and third\nclasses will embark on the several\nships of the cruising squadron for the\nannual winter croise. The class to\n'be graduated, will be the largest that\n\u2018ever left the institnton at any one\ntime before. It contains 200 mem\nbers. The oclass of 1907 was larger\nby eight members than this year's\nclass, but was graduated in three\nseparate divisions, one section of\ne\nd\nTANDARD\nlspeciat TALKING MACHINES\ni b \u201cAn l E Y MERCANTILE CO. We are still g?ing ;.hem aw:;;\nBeuutiful Florence in blue prin and will continue to do so unti\nThese pillow tops